'''Omar Khaled Mohamed Abdelsalam Marmoush''' ({{langx|arz|عمر خالد محمد عبد السلام مرموش}};<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.masress.com/youm7/5614439 |title=الثامنة يا أبطال.. عمر مرموش الموهبة الصاعدة فى كتيبة |trans-title=Eighth, O heroes.. Omar Marmoush, the rising talent in the battalion |website=Masress |date=11 January 2022 |access-date=18 February 2025 |language=ar}}</ref> born 7 February 1999) is an Egyptian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{English football updater|ManchesC}} club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] and the [[Egypt national football team|Egypt national team]].

==Club career==
===Wadi Degla===
Marmoush made his professional debut for [[Wadi Degla SC|Wadi Degla]] in the [[Egyptian Premier League]] on 8 July 2016, coming on as a substitute in the match against [[Al Ittihad Alexandria Club]], which finished as a 3–2 win. In total, he made sixteen league appearances for Wadi Degla and scored two goals, before moving to [[VfL Wolfsburg II]] in 2017.<ref name="Wadi">{{cite news |last=Al-Awadi |first=Hani |url=https://www.filgoal.com/articles/361300 |title=حوار في الجول – عمر مرموش يوضح لماذا فضل فولفسبورج على دورتموند.. وكيف تألق مع دجلة |trans-title=Conversation with FilGoal – Omar Marmoush explains why he favoured Wolfsburg over Dortmund... and how he starred with Degla |website=FilGoal.com |date=11 April 2019 |access-date=16 May 2020 |language=ar}}</ref>

===VfL Wolfsburg===
On 26 May 2020, Marmoush made his professional debut for Wolfsburg in their 4–1 [[Bundesliga]] win over [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] at the [[BayArena]]. Marmoush signed his first professional contract for the club on 23 June. On 5 August 2020, he made his European debut in a 3–0 defeat (5–1 aggregate) against [[FC Shakhtar Donetsk|Shakhtar Donetsk]] in the [[UEFA Europa League]] round of 16. Marmoush returned to Wolfsburg after his breakthrough Bundesliga season with Stuttgart.{{citation needed|date=February 2025}}

On 5 January 2021, Marmoush was loaned to [[FC St. Pauli]] for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.vfl-wolfsburg.de/en/news-detail/news-detail/detail/news/loaned-to-st-pauli/|title=Loaned to St. Pauli|publisher=VfL Wolfsburg|date=5 January 2021|access-date=5 January 2021}}</ref> He played 21 games and scored seven goals for the club.{{citation needed|date=February 2025}}

On 30 August 2021, Marmoush was loaned out to [[VfB Stuttgart]] until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2122/leihe-omar-marmoush-kopie/|title=Omar Marmoush joins VfB on loan|publisher=VfB Stuttgart|date=30 August 2021|access-date=30 August 2021}}</ref> He scored a last minute equaliser against Eintracht Frankfurt on his debut. He was later named [[Bundesliga]] rookie of the month for September 2021. On 11 December 2021, Marmoush faced his parent club Wolfsburg and assisted [[Konstantinos Mavropanos]]'s goal and in the 79th minute, Marmoush stepped up to take a penalty and he missed by hitting his [[Panenka (penalty kick)|panenka]] attempt off the crossbar. Marmoush was also named Bundesliga Rookie of the Month for March 2022.<ref name="Bundesliga Rookie of the Month">{{cite web |title=Bundesliga-Rookies aus Cannstatt |url=https://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/aktuell/neues/profis/2122/bundesliga-rookies-aus-cannstatt/ |website=vfb.de/de |access-date=15 March 2022 |language=German}}</ref> He completed his loan spell having scored three goals in 21 games.{{citation needed|date=February 2025}}

On 30 July 2022, Marmoush scored his first goal for Wolfsburg in a 1–0 first round [[DFB-Pokal]] match against [[FC Carl Zeiss Jena|Carl Zeiss Jena]]. Marmoush scored his first [[Bundesliga]] goal for the club in a 3–2 win over his former loan club VFB Stuttgart. On 24 January 2023, Marmoush scored his first goal in 2023 in a 5–0 rout over relegation strugglers [[Hertha BSC]]. Marmoush haunted his former club Stuttgart again, as he scored the only goal in a 1–0 win at the [[MHPArena]]. Marmoush finished the season with 36 appearances, six goals and one assist in all competitions.{{citation needed|date=February 2025}}

===Eintracht Frankfurt===
====2023–24 season====
On 15 May 2023, it was announced that Marmoush would join [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] on a [[Free transfer (association football)|free transfer]] ahead of the [[2023–24 Eintracht Frankfurt season|2023–24 season]], and wear the number seven shirt.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Omar Marmoush joins Eintracht |url=https://en.eintracht.de/news/eintracht-verpflichtet-omar-marmoush-150481 |access-date=2023-05-15 |website=Eintracht Frankfurt |language=en}}</ref> On 13 August, Marmoush scored his first goal for Eintracht Frankfurt in a 7–0 win over [[1. FC Lokomotive Leipzig]] in the first round of the [[DFB-Pokal]]. On 27 August 2023, Marmoush scored his first [[Bundesliga]] goal for the club in a 1–1 draw against [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]]. On 21 September, he scored his first goal in European competitions from a penalty in a 2–1 win over [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]] during the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa Conference League|Europa Conference League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/6/53/508855/Sports/Talents-Abroad/Egypt-Marmoush-scores-in-Frankfurt;s-Conference-Le.aspx |title=Egypt Marmoush scores in Frankfurt's Conference League win over Aberdeen |publisher=Ahram Online |date=21 September 2023 }}</ref>

Marmoush scored 16 goals in 37 appearances in all competitions in his debut season. He attracted transfer interest from [[Premier League]] clubs such as [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle]] and [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham]] thanks to his magnificent debut season for ''Die Adler''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tribalfootball.com/article/soccer-premier-league-arsenal-liverpool-join-interest-in-eintracht-frankfurt-striker-marmoush-c03d6f44-3bae-4267-a97d-44827e1eae39 |title=Arsenal, Liverpool join interest in Eintracht Frankfurt striker Marmoush |publisher=Tribal Football |date=15 September 2024 }}</ref> Marmoush scored a brace in Frankfurt's 3–3 draw with [[Borussia Dortmund]] and a goal in their thumping 5–1 win against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern]]. With 12 goals in the [[2023–24 Bundesliga|2023–24 season]], Marmoush became the third-highest African goal scorer in Bundesliga.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://africanfolder.com/top-african-goal-scorers-in-bundesliga-2023-2024/|title=Top African Goal Scorers In Bundesliga 2023/2024|website=[[African Folder]] |language=EN |date=21 May 2024}}</ref> Marmoush scored a crucial penalty against [[RB Leipzig]] to tie the match 2–2 to help Frankfurt qualify for the [[2024–25 UEFA Europa League|2024–25 Europa League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/677582/rb-leipzig-eintracht-frankfurt |title=Eintracht Frankfurt 2–2 RB Leipzig |publisher=ESPN |date=18 May 2024 }}</ref>

====2024–25 season====
Marmoush contributed six goals and three assists in September, which earned him the Bundesliga Player of the Month award.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.eintracht.de/news/bundesliga-marmoush-ist-player-of-the-month-september-2024-162452 |title=Marmoush crowned Bundesliga Player of the Month |publisher=Eintracht Frankfurt |date=17 October 2024 }}</ref> During that month, he scored a brace in a 2–1 victory against his former club [[VfL Wolfsburg]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.eintracht.de/news/doppelpack-marmoush-eintracht-siegt-161474 |title=Marmoush brace clinches away win |publisher=Eintracht Frankfurt |date=14 September 2024 }}</ref> and provided decisive goals in matches against [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]] and [[Holstein Kiel]], overtaking [[Harry Kane]] as the league's top scorer during this period.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/can-eintracht-frankfurt-s-omar-marmoush-dethrone-bayern-munich-s-harry-kane-29177 |title=Can Eintracht Frankfurt's Omar Marmoush dethrone Bayern Munich's Harry Kane? |publisher=Bundesliga |date=1 October 2024 }}</ref>

In the [[2024–25 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]], Marmoush made significant contributions, including a penalty against [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Besiktas]] and free-kick goals against [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]]. His ability to score from set pieces was highlighted by three consecutive free-kick goals in November.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/omar-marmoush-3-free-kicks-in-row-messi-record-frankfurt-29710 |title=Eintracht Frankfurt's Omar Marmoush takes star free-kick power to the next level |publisher=Bundesliga |date=21 November 202}}</ref>

Marmoush completed the first half of the [[2024–25 Bundesliga]] season as the second top scorer, behind Kane, with 15 goals, breaking his club's previous record for the ''Hinrunde'' set by [[Theofanis Gekas]] in the 2010–11 season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/omar-marmoush-and-eintracht-frankfurt-set-records-egypt-ekitike-freiburg-30448 |title=Omar Marmoush and Eintracht Frankfurt set Hinrunde records |publisher=Bundesliga |date=15 January 2025 }}</ref>

===Manchester City===
====2024–25 season====
On 23 January 2025, [[Premier League]] club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] announced the signing of Marmoush on a four-and-a-half-year deal for a reported fee of £59&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/manchester-city-sign-omar-marmoush-63873209 |title=City seal signing of Omar Marmoush |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=23 January 2025 |access-date=23 January 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cx2kxyyd8e0o |title=Man City sign Frankfurt forward Marmoush for £59m |website=[[BBC Sport]] |date=23 January 2025 |access-date=23 January 2025}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 25 January in a 3–1 home league win over [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/manchester-city-v-chelsea-premier-league-match-report-january-2025-63873419 |title=Haaland and Foden fire City to key victory over Chelsea |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=25 January 2025 |access-date=26 January 2025}}</ref> On 15 February, he scored three goals for City in a 4–0 home league win over [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]], netting his first career [[hat-trick]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Stone |first=Simon |date=15 February 2025 |title=Manchester City 4–0 Newcastle United: Omar Marmoush hits hat-trick in thumping win |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c2k57y0dnnyt |access-date=15 February 2025 |website=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]]}}</ref> Marmoush scored his first [[FA Cup]] goal on 30 March as a substitute for [[Erling Haaland]], netting the winner in a 2–1 away victory over [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] in the [[2024–25 FA Cup#Quarter-finals|quarter-finals]], sending City through to their seventh straight FA Cup [[2024–25 FA Cup#Semi-finals|semi-final]].<ref>{{cite web |last=McNulty |first=Phil |date=30 March 2025 |title= AFC Bournemouth 1–2 Manchester City|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c07z3l1g2p4t |access-date=30 March 2025 |website=BBC Sport}}</ref> However, he missed a penalty kick in the final.<ref>{{cite web |last=Braidwood |first=Jamie |date=17 May 2025 |title=Why didn't Erling Haaland take Man City's penalty in FA Cup final? |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/erling-haaland-omar-marmoush-penalty-man-city-wembley-b2752981.html |access-date=22 May 2025 |website=The Independent}}</ref> On 20 May, Marmoush opened the scoring in City's 3–1 home win against Bournemouth in the Premier League, a long range effort that went into the top corner of [[Kepa Arrizabalaga]]'s goal via the post.<ref>{{cite news |last=Hafeez |first=Shamoon |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/crmk7lgj7gjt |title=Man City 3–1 Bournemouth: Marmoush, Silva and Gonzalez score for hosts |website=BBC Sport |date=20 May 2025 |access-date=31 May 2025}}</ref> On 31 May, it was announced that the goal had won the [[Premier League Goal of the Season]] award.<ref name="goal">{{cite news |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/4322208 |title=Marmoush wins Guinness Goal of the Season award |publisher=Premier League |date=31 May 2025 |access-date=31 May 2025}}</ref>

====2025–26 season====
On 29 October 2025, Marmoush scored his first goal of the [[2025–26 Manchester City F.C. season|2025–26 season]] in a 3–1 win over [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] in the fourth round of the [[2025–26 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/13459732/swansea-1-3-man-city-omar-marmoushs-late-strike-spares-pep-guardiolas-blushes-after-early-scare|title=Swansea 1-3 Man City: Omar Marmoush's late strike spares Pep Guardiola's blushes after early scare |date=29 October 2025|access-date=1 March 2026|website=Sky Sports}}</ref>

After returning from the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations|Africa Cup of Nations]] with Egypt, he scored his first [[2025–26 Premier League|Premier League]] goal of the season in a 2–0 win over [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] on 24 January 2026.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-vs-wolves-live-33294816|title=Man City vs Wolves highlights and reaction as Omar Marmoush and Antoine Semenyo win it|date=24 January 2026|access-date=1 March 2026|website=Manchester Evening News}}</ref> On 4 February, he scored twice in a 3–1 win over Newcastle United in the second leg of the EFL Cup semi-final.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2026/feb/04/manchester-city-v-newcastle-united-carabao-cup-semi-final-second-leg-live|title=Manchester City 3-1 Newcastle United (agg 5-1): Carabao Cup semi-final, second leg – as it happened|date=4 February 2026|access-date=1 March 2026|website=The Guardian}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:عمر مرموش.jpg|thumb|Marmoush with [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]] in 2022]]

Marmoush was included in [[Egypt national under-20 football team|Egypt]]'s [[2017 Africa U-20 Cup of Nations squads#Egypt|squad]] for the [[2017 Africa U-20 Cup of Nations]] in Zambia. He made two appearances during the tournament, in which Egypt were eliminated in the group stage.<ref name="WF">{{WorldFootball.net}}</ref>

Marmoush was also eligible to play for [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/player/omar-marmoush |title=Omar Marmoush |publisher=Bundesliga |access-date=17 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250117121532/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/player/omar-marmoush |archive-date=17 January 2025 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcstpauli.com/en/news/published/new-boy-omar-marmoush-on-his-start-at-fcsp/|title=New boy Omar Marmoush on his start at FCSP|website=FC St. Pauli}}</ref> before becoming [[cap-tied]] with the [[Egypt national football team|Egyptian national team]] in October 2021.

On 8 October 2021, Marmoush made his debut for the Egypt national team and scored the only goal in a 1–0 victory over Libya.<ref>{{cite web|title=Egypt – Libya 1:0 (WC Qualifiers Africa 2019–2021, Group F)|url=https://www.worldfootball.net/match-report/ma9044191/lineup/|access-date=8 October 2021|website=WorldFootball.net}}</ref>

On 29 December 2021, Marmoush was named in Egypt's [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations squads#Egypt|28-man squad]] for the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Ali|first=Ahmad Gamal|date=29 December 2021|title=Mohamed Salah leads Egypt squad for the Africa Cup of Nations|url=https://www.kingfut.com/2021/12/29/mohamed-salah-leads-egypt-squad-for-the-africa-cup-of-nations/|access-date=29 December 2021|website=KingFut}}</ref> He played in all three [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations Group D|group stage matches]], as well as all four knockout ties en route to the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations Final|final]] against [[Senegal national football team|Senegal, which]] ended in a 4–2 loss on penalties for Egypt.<ref>{{cite web|last=Football|first=CAF-Confedération Africaine du|title=CAFOnline.com|url=https://www.cafonline.com/total-africa-cup-of-nations/matches/2021/2243301/|access-date=5 February 2022|website=CAFOnline}}</ref>

On 19 March 2022, Marmoush was called up for Egypt's [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – CAF third round|2022 FIFA World Cup qualification third round]] matches against Senegal.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Soliman |first=Seif |date=19 March 2022 |title=Afsha returns, Sherif excluded as Egypt squad for Senegal World Cup qualifiers revealed |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2022/03/19/afsha-returns-sherif-egypt-squad-senegal/ |access-date=24 March 2022 |website=KingFut}}</ref> He played in both matches as Egypt were defeated 3–1 on penalties and knocked out of World Cup contention.<ref>{{cite web |title=Senegal vs. Egypt – Football Match Summary – March 29, 2022 |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/629216 |access-date=31 March 2022 |publisher=ESPN}}</ref> On 27 September, Marmoush scored the opening goal as Egypt beat [[Liberia national football team|Liberia]] 3–0 in a friendly match.<ref>{{cite web |title=Egypt vs. Liberia |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/09/27/world/friendlies/egypt/liberia/3954608/ |access-date=30 September 2022 |website=Soccerway}}</ref>

On 24 March 2023, Marmoush scored the second goal for Egypt in a 2–0 victory over [[Malawi national football team|Malawi]] during the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Khaled |first=Mahmoud |date=25 March 2023 |title=Two first-half goals see Egypt beat Malawi in AFCON qualifiers |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2023/03/25/egypt-beat-malawi-qualifiers/ |access-date=26 March 2023 |website=KingFut }}</ref> Four days later, he scored in a 4–0 away victory over the same opponent.<ref>{{cite news |title=LIVE: Malawi v Egypt (2023 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers) |url=https://english.ahram.org.eg/News/492577.aspx |access-date=28 March 2023 |website=Ahram Online}}</ref> At the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]], Marmoush scored the equaliser in a 2–2 draw against [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]] to help Egypt qualify for the last 16.<ref>{{citation|title=Marmoush plays hero for Salah-less Egypt in 2–2 draw with Ghana|date=18 January 2024 |url=https://bulinews.com/news/20053/marmoush-plays-hero-for-salah-less-egypt-2-2-draw-ghana|access-date=18 January 2025}}</ref>

On 2 December 2025, Marmoush was called up to the Egypt squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/egypt-name-final-28-man-squad-for-totalenergies-caf-afcon-2025-salah-leads-pharaohs-charge/|title=Egypt name final 28-man squad for TotalEnergies CAF AFCON 2025, Salah leads Pharaohs' charge|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=2 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref> He scored twice at the tournament as Egypt reached the semi-finals, losing to eventual winners Senegal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.olympics.com/en/news/afcon-2025-egypt-results-scorers-and-standing-full-list|title=AFCON 2025: Egypt results, scorers and standing - full list|date=18 January 2026|access-date=1 March 2026|website=Olympics}}</ref> On 17 January 2026, in the third-place play-off against [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]], Marmoush was one of two Egyptian players to have their kicks saved in a 4–2 penalty shootout loss.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.in/football/match/_/gameId/732183/nigeria-egito|title=Egypt 0-0 Nigeria (17 Jan, 2026) Final Score|access-date=1 March 2026|website=ESPN}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Besides his [[Egyptian citizenship]], Marmoush holds [[Canadian citizenship]] through his [[Egyptian Canadian]] parents who lived in Canada for six years before resettling in [[Cairo]], where Marmoush was raised and started playing youth football with the [[Wadi Degla SC|Wadi Degla youth academy]].<ref name="bundesliga">{{cite web | title=Omar Marmoush: Who is Eintracht Frankfurt's Egyptian striker with links to Mo Salah and Alphonso Davies? | website=Bundesliga | date=30 September 2024 | url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/who-is-omar-marmoush-eintracht-frankfurt-egypt-canada-forward-salah-davies-17290 | access-date=2024-10-25}}</ref> He lived in the [[Maadi|Maadi neighbourhood]] in Cairo, Egypt.

Marmoush is a [[Muslims|Muslim]]. He is often seen doing the [[sujud]] after scoring a goal.<ref>{{Cite web |date=29 September 2024 |title=Marmoush keeps scoring as Frankfurt keeps winning in the Bundesliga |url=https://apnews.com/article/marmoush-frankfurt-kiel-bundesliga-scores-01cc4c2cf6a50ccbd7a176e7fb741b83 |access-date=2025-02-14 |website=AP News |language=en}}</ref>

